Default to space for jump

Unlike the others, this patch is not a bug fix. It deliberately changes the
game's behaviour, and is kept separate so that is obvious in review.

The original ships ctrl as the jump key, which was ordinary in 1992 and is not
any more -- space has been the platformer convention for decades. It is also
the binding least likely to be fought over by a window manager: macOS claims
control with every arrow key for Mission Control, so the original default
cannot be combined with movement there at all.

Space is free during play. The game reads it in menus, to begin a new game, and
in dialogs, where it hurries the typewriter effect along, but ProcessGameInput
never looks at it, so nothing in-game is displaced.

Bomb stays on alt, which nothing claims.

Anyone who prefers the original can set it back from the game's own Keyboard
Redefine menu, and the choice is saved to COSMO1.CFG.

diff --git a/game2.c b/game2.c
index 6c7fa20..8018c95 100644
--- a/game2.c
+++ b/game2.c
@@ -2960,7 +2960,8 @@ void LoadConfigurationData(char *filename)
         scancodeSouth = SCANCODE_KP_2;
         scancodeWest = SCANCODE_KP_4;
         scancodeEast = SCANCODE_KP_6;
-        scancodeJump = SCANCODE_CTRL;
+        /* PORT: space rather than the original's ctrl; see patches/0007. */
+        scancodeJump = SCANCODE_SPACE;
         scancodeBomb = SCANCODE_ALT;
         isMusicEnabled = true;
         isSoundEnabled = true;
